<div itemprop="articleBody">
<h3>Tutorial 21. Finishing the Cups. Sewing the Lace Inset. </h3>
<p></p>
<p><strong>I have sewn the other cup in place.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image002.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I take narrow lace ribbons to finish the top edges of both cups. </strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image004.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image006.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image008.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I finish the top edge of the second cup as well.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image010.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image012.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>Then I trim the excess off the seam allowances, bend the lace back, pin it down</strong> and secure it with neat hand stitches.&nbsp; </p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image014.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>Now we only need to press it all. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image016.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></strong></p>
<p><strong>We also need to work on the central piece of the lace inset at the top of the dress. </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image018.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I join the lace with its mesh backing.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image020.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image022.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image024.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image026.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image028.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image030.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image032.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image034.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>The lace inset aligns with the cups perfectly.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image036.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>You should just pin it down from the inner side and sew it on by hand. </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%204/transcripts/Tutorial%2021_files/image038.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>

</div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
